sk what does the customer need  what does the customer want  who is this customerwe will also explore the various ways in which marketing departments and independent agencies answer these questions – whether through research analysis or even trialanderror  once a company identifies its customer and product marketers must then determine the best way to capture the customer’s attention  capturing the customer’s attention may entail undercutting competitors on price aggressively marketing a product with promotions and advertising as with “as seen on tv” ads or specifically targeting ideal customers as with custom yacht building  the strategy a marketing firm chooses for a particular product is absolutely vital to the success of the product  the idea that “great products sell themselves” is simply not true  by the end of this course you will be familiar with the art and science of marketing a product   name description time price     reading principles of marketing “chapter  what is marketing”   free view in itunes   reading university of georgia john burnett’s core concepts of marketing “the marketing mix”   free view in itunes   reading principles of marketing “chapter  developing and managing offerings”   free view in itunes   reading university of georgia john burnett’s core concepts of marketing “chapter  pricing the product”   free view in itunes   reading principles of marketing “chapter  price the only revenue generator   free view in itunes   reading steven van hook’s “pricing key influences on what you can charge”   free view in itunes   reading university of georgia john burnett’s core concepts of marketing “the market is a place”   free view in itunes   reading principles of marketing “chapter  advertising integrated marketing c   free view in itunes  class b  marketing continued class b  marketing continued  free view in itunes   reading principles of marketing “chapter  market segmenting targeting and posi   free view in itunes   reading university of geor